nages individual lines in a Linux file."},{"pos":[1086,1154],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>nxGroup Resource<ept id=\"p1\">](lnxGroupResource.md)</ept>--Manages local Linux groups.","source":"[nxGroup Resource](lnxGroupResource.md)--Manages local Linux groups."},{"pos":[1158,1235],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>nxPackage Resource<ept id=\"p1\">](lnxPackageResource.md)</ept>--Manages packages on Linux nodes.","source":"[nxPackage Resource](lnxPackageResource.md)--Manages packages on Linux nodes."},{"pos":[1238,1310],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>nxScript Resource<ept id=\"p1\">](lnxScriptResource.md)</ept>--Runs scripts on target nodes.","source":"[nxScript Resource](lnxScriptResource.md)--Runs scripts on target nodes."},{"pos":[1313,1391],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>nxService Resource<ept id=\"p1\">](lnxServiceResource.md)</ept>--Manages Linux services (daemons).","source":"[nxService Resource](lnxServiceResource.md)--Manages Linux services (daemons)."},{"pos":[1394,1500],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>nxSshAuthorizedKeys Resource<ept id=\"p1\">](lnxSshAuthorizedKeysResource.md)</ept>--Manages public ssh keys for a Linux user.","source":"[nxSshAuthorizedKeys Resource](lnxSshAuthorizedKeysResource.md)--Manages public ssh keys for a Linux user."},{"pos":[1504,1569],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>nxUser Resource<ept id=\"p1\">](lnxUserResource.md)</ept>--Manages local Linux users.","source":"[nxUser Resource](lnxUserResource.md)--Manages local Linux users."}],"content":"---\ntitle:   Built-In Desired State Configuration Resources for Linux\nms.date:  2016-05-16\nkeywords:  powershell,DSC\ndescription:  \nms.topic:  article\nauthor:  eslesar\nmanager:  dongill\nms.prod:  powershell\n---\n\n# Built-In Desired State Configuration Resources for Linux\n\nResources are building blocks that you can use to write a PowerShell Desired State Configuration (DSC) script. DSC for Linux comes with a set of built-in functionality for configuring resources such as files and folders, packages, environment variables, and services and processes.\n\n## Built-in resources \n\nThe following table provides a list of these resources and links to topics that describe them in detail.\n\n* [nxArchive Resource](lnxArchiveResource.md)--Provides a mechanism to unpack archive (.tar, .zip) files at a specific path.\n* [nxEnvironment Resource](lnxEnvironmentResource.md)--Manages environment variables on target nodes. \n* [nxFile Resource](lnxFileResource.md)--Manages Linux files and directories. \n* [nxFileLine Resource](lnxFileLineResource.md)--Manages individual lines in a Linux file. \n* [nxGroup Resource](lnxGroupResource.md)--Manages local Linux groups. \n* [nxPackage Resource](lnxPackageResource.md)--Manages packages on Linux nodes.\n* [nxScript Resource](lnxScriptResource.md)--Runs scripts on target nodes.\n* [nxService Resource](lnxServiceResource.md)--Manages Linux services (daemons).\n* [nxSshAuthorizedKeys Resource](lnxSshAuthorizedKeysResource.md)--Manages public ssh keys for a Linux user. \n* [nxUser Resource](lnxUserResource.md)--Manages local Linux users. \n  \n"}